{
  "name": "RPlog_To_Hire_a_Smuggler_Part_three",
  "title": "Sealing the Privateer's Contract",
  "summary": "Late at night in a chilly NR embassy office, Ambassador Ambrosia Ad-Delgard rouses the bleary, hard-drinking Rattataki smuggler Captain Shiari Vane over a holocom to finalize their arrangement. The two trade dry barbs and mutual toasts -- caf-laced flask against mystery bottle -- before getting to business: the Republic will pardon Vane's earlier 'misunderstanding' over an already-acquired ship, exchanging it for a newer vessel that comes with an open privateering contract. Ambrosia lays out the terms -- no slaving, no illegal substances in Republic space, no turning the ship against its benefactors -- and a ten percent bounty on Imperial supplies intercepted and delivered as aid to blockaded Caspar, ideally before the cargo enters the blockade itself. Vane, who professes genuine scruples against slavers, agrees and proposes exchanging vessels on Tatooine. The deal sealed with a final round of toasts, Ambrosia promises pick-up details to follow and warns the captain to be careful, the Caspians having no margin for further losses.",
